The Federal Reserve will purchaseapproximately one billion dlrs of U.S. Treasury bills for acustomer after the Treasury's auction of four-year notes, a Fedspokesman said.    The spokesman said the Fed intends to purchase billsmaturing in up to six months.    Dealers said Federal funds were trading at 6-3/16 pct whenthe Fed announced the operation. Many had expected to Fed tobuy bills for itself, thereby adding permanent reserves to thebanking system. Since it did not do so today, this Fed move islikely tomorrow. Reuter&#3;